  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_7' aria-label=\" Larsen and Toubro Limited versus Puri Construction Pvt. Ltd. and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('7','2025','2025_4_2811_2850','2025INSC523'); ><font size='4'> <strong>LARSEN AND TOUBRO LIMITED<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>PURI CONSTRUCTION PVT. LTD. AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2811</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 523</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007392025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PANKAJ MITHAL</strong><br> Issue for Consideration In petition u/s.34, Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, Single Judge had set aside the Arbitral Award. Division Bench in appeal thereagainst u/s.37, Arbitration Act by way of the impugned judgment, inter alia upheld the dismissal of L&amp;T&rsquo;s counter-claim findings of the Arbitral Tribunal that the Supplementary Agreement was a non-starter as it was vitiated by economic duress; that the Development Agreement was not novated by the Supplementary Agreement; that L&amp;T committed fundamental breach of the Development Agreement. The operative part of<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 21-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 2575/2016</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('7','2025','2025_4_2811_2850','2025INSC523','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split